CAPE TOWN – Egyptian swimmer Farida Osman won the ‘Best Female Athlete from Africa’ gong at the ANOC Awards 2017 in Prague at the Forum Karlin on Thursday night. The Best Male Athlete for Africa is @chadleclos! --#LIVE from @ANOC_Olympic Awards 2017! @fina1908 @teamsa17 pic.twitter.com/83srHUZdp8 South African swimmer Chad Le Clos was named ‘Best Male Athlete from Africa 2017’ to complete a clean sweep for the continent’s finest swimmers. The Association Of National Olympic Committees (ANOC) honoured the best male and best female athletes on five continents.  African News Agency